19 Romam magnique] The first epithet insists on the national character, the second on the religious priority of the festival, as dedicated to Jupiter. Although Livy gives the two epithets as inter· changeable, it is probable that magni should really be applied to any games performed in fulfilment of a vow to Jupiter, Romani to these particular games when they became regular (annu2): but there was a certain similarity in the programme.
